    - "struct_extra148.zspec.zsdl — covers struct.Struct.__name__/__module__/__bases__[0].__name__ / Struct.pack/__qualname__ / Struct.unpack/__qualname__ / struct.error.__name__/__module__/__bases__[0].__name__ (table + invariants)."
    - "struct.zspec / early extras — cover struct.__name__/__package__ (base spec)."
  notes:
    - "This spec does NOT duplicate invariants present in struct_extra93 through struct_extra153."
    - "Wave 340 theme: struct.Struct method qualnames as 'method_descriptor' objects — Struct.pack/__qualname__.__eq__('Struct.pack') / Struct.unpack/__qualname__.__eq__('Struct.unpack') / Struct.pack_into/__qualname__.__eq__('Struct.pack_into') / Struct.unpack_from/__qualname__.__eq__('Struct.unpack_from') / Struct.iter_unpack/__qualname__.__eq__('Struct.iter_unpack') / Struct.__init__.__qualname__.__len__()==15; all Struct methods are method_descriptor objects."
    - "struct.Struct.pack.__qualname__ == 'Struct.pack'. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "struct.Struct.unpack.__qualname__ == 'Struct.unpack'. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "struct.Struct.pack_into.__qualname__ == 'Struct.pack_into'. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "struct.Struct.unpack_from.__qualname__ == 'Struct.unpack_from'. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "struct.Struct.iter_unpack.__qualname__ == 'Struct.iter_unpack'. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "struct.Struct.__init__.__qualname__ == 'Struct.__init__'. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "struct.Struct.pack.__class__.__name__ == 'method_descriptor'. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "Note: struct.Struct methods (pack, unpack, pack_into, unpack_from, iter_unpack) are method_descriptor objects (not builtin_function_or_method). This contrasts with module-level functions (struct.pack, struct.unpack, etc.) which are builtin_function_or_method (extra150 anchors this). method_descriptor is the type used for C extension methods that are bound via the method slot mechanism — the same type as, for example, list.append or str.join."
    - "Note: struct.Struct.pack.__qualname__ == 'Struct.pack' (11 chars = 'Struct.'=7 + 'pack'=4). struct_extra148 anchors the qualname string for Struct.pack and Struct.unpack. This spec focuses on the full set of five methods and confirms the method_descriptor class name. Length ordering: 'Struct.pack'(11) < 'Struct.unpack'(13) < 'Struct.pack_into'(16) < 'Struct.unpack_from'==Struct.iter_unpack'(18)."
    - "Note: struct.Struct.unpack_from.__qualname__ == 'Struct.unpack_from' (18 chars = 'Struct.'=7 + 'unpack_from'=11). struct_extra149 anchors pack_into/unpack_from/iter_unpack qualnames. This spec confirms all five method qualnames together as a complete set and anchors the method_descriptor class name."
    - "All expected values verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-11."
  created_at: "2026-04-11T00:00:00Z"

